---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Research — Efe Ertugrul">
	<main>
		<header>
			<h1>Research</h1>
			<p class="intro">
				Efe Ertugrul works at the intersection of infrastructure and scientific reproducibility—building systems that make bioimaging and biomedical data interoperable, standardized, and production-ready.
			</p>
		</header>

		<section class="research-entry">
			<h2>Bioimaging Metadata & Schema Translation</h2>
			<div class="meta">
				<span><a href="https://www.umassmed.edu/strambiolab/personnel/current-lab-members/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Strambio Lab</a> / QUAREP-LiMi / UMass Chan Medical School</span>
			</div>
			<p class="problem">
				<strong>Problem:</strong> Microscopy metadata is fragmented across incompatible standards (OME, NBO-Q, vendor-specific formats). Researchers can't query, validate, or share imaging data reliably across platforms.
			</p>
			<p>
				<strong>What I'm doing:</strong> Building automated pipelines to translate OME and NBO-Q XSD schemas into LinkML schema definitions. This enables unified metadata models, cross-platform validation, and ontology-backed data harmonization.
			</p>
			<p>
				<strong>Impact:</strong> Enables reproducible imaging workflows that comply with FAIR data principles. Delivered a talk on this work at the 2025 OME Community Congress (MBL Woods Hole).
			</p>
			<div class="links">
				<a href="https://github.com/ome-nbo-tools/ome-nbo-formatter" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Code</a>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="research-entry">
			<h2>Schema Translation Pipelines</h2>
			<div class="meta">
				<span>LinkML / XSD → Graph Models</span>
			</div>

			<svg class="diagram" viewBox="0 0 600 120" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
				<rect x="20" y="35" width="100" height="50" rx="4" stroke="#111827" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none"/>
				<text x="70" y="65" text-anchor="middle" font-size="14" fill="#111827" font-weight="500">XSD</text>
				
				<path d="M 120 60 L 160 60" stroke="#111827" stroke-width="1.5" marker-end="url(#arrowhead)"/>
				
				<rect x="160" y="20" width="120" height="80" rx="4" stroke="#111827" stroke-width="1.5" fill="rgba(255,255,255,0.5)"/>
				<text x="220" y="45" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" fill="#374151" font-weight="500">Parse</text>
				<text x="220" y="65" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" fill="#374151" font-weight="500">Transform</text>
				<text x="220" y="85" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" fill="#374151" font-weight="500">Validate</text>
				
				<path d="M 280 60 L 320 60" stroke="#111827" stroke-width="1.5" marker-end="url(#arrowhead)"/>
				
				<rect x="320" y="35" width="100" height="50" rx="4" stroke="#111827" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none"/>
				<text x="370" y="65" text-anchor="middle" font-size="14" fill="#111827" font-weight="500">LinkML</text>
				
				<path d="M 420 60 L 460 60" stroke="#111827" stroke-width="1.5" marker-end="url(#arrowhead)"/>
				
				<rect x="460" y="35" width="120" height="50" rx="4" stroke="#111827" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none"/>
				<text x="520" y="65" text-anchor="middle" font-size="14" fill="#111827" font-weight="500">Ontologies</text>
				
				<defs>
					<marker id="arrowhead" markerWidth="10" markerHeight="10" refX="9" refY="3" orient="auto">
						<polygon points="0 0, 10 3, 0 6" fill="#111827"/>
					</marker>
				</defs>
			</svg>

			<p class="problem">
				<strong>Problem:</strong> Converting complex XML schemas (XSD) to modern data modeling frameworks is manual, error-prone, and blocks interoperability efforts in bioinformatics.
			</p>
			<p>
				<strong>Approach:</strong> Developed extensible tooling in Python for automated XSD parsing, transformation rules, and LinkML schema generation. Built validation layers to ensure semantic consistency across source and target formats.
			</p>
			<p>
				<strong>Why it matters:</strong> Accelerates metadata standardization efforts across imaging, genomics, and clinical research domains.
			</p>
			<div class="links">
				<a href="https://github.com/ome-nbo-tools/ome-nbo-formatter" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Code</a>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="research-entry">
			<h2>FAIR Data & Ontology Integration</h2>
			<div class="meta">
				<span>Biomedical Imaging Informatics</span>
			</div>

			<svg class="diagram" viewBox="0 0 400 200" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
				<defs>
					<marker id="arrow2" markerWidth="8" markerHeight="8" refX="7" refY="3" orient="auto">
						<polygon points="0 0, 8 3, 0 6" fill="#111827"/>
					</marker>
				</defs>
				
				<text x="200" y="20" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" fill="#6b7280" font-weight="600">FAIR Principles</text>
				
				<rect x="20" y="40" width="80" height="120" rx="4" stroke="#111827" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none"/>
				<text x="60" y="55" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#111827" font-weight="600">Findable</text>
				<text x="60" y="75" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#374151">Metadata</text>
				<text x="60" y="90" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#374151">Persistent IDs</text>
				<text x="60" y="105" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#374151">Searchable</text>
				
				<rect x="120" y="40" width="80" height="120" rx="4" stroke="#111827" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none"/>
				<text x="160" y="55" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#111827" font-weight="600">Accessible</text>
				<text x="160" y="75" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#374151">Standard</text>
				<text x="160" y="90" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#374151">protocols</text>
				<text x="160" y="105" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#374151">Auth when</text>
				<text x="160" y="118" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#374151">needed</text>
				
				<rect x="220" y="40" width="80" height="120" rx="4" stroke="#111827" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none"/>
				<text x="260" y="55" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#111827" font-weight="600">Interoperable</text>
				<text x="260" y="75" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#374151">Standard</text>
				<text x="260" y="90" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#374151">vocabularies</text>
				<text x="260" y="105" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#374151">LinkML/RDF</text>
				
				<rect x="320" y="40" width="60" height="120" rx="4" stroke="#111827" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none"/>
				<text x="350" y="55" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#111827" font-weight="600">Reusable</text>
				<text x="350" y="75" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#374151">Rich</text>
				<text x="350" y="90" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#374151">metadata</text>
				<text x="350" y="105" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#374151">Clear</text>
				<text x="350" y="118" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#374151">license</text>
				
				<path d="M 100 100 L 120 100" stroke="#111827" stroke-width="1" marker-end="url(#arrow2)"/>
				<path d="M 200 100 L 220 100" stroke="#111827" stroke-width="1" marker-end="url(#arrow2)"/>
				<path d="M 300 100 L 320 100" stroke="#111827" stroke-width="1" marker-end="url(#arrow2)"/>
				
				<text x="200" y="185" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b7280">Ontology-backed metadata → cross-study integration</text>
			</svg>

			<p class="problem">
				<strong>Problem:</strong> Scientific datasets are difficult to find, access, integrate, and reuse because metadata lacks semantic structure and controlled vocabularies.
			</p>
			<p>
				<strong>Contribution:</strong> Implementing FAIR principles through LinkML, connecting bioimaging metadata to biomedical ontologies (e.g., Cell Ontology, Uberon), enabling structured queries and cross-study integration.
			</p>
			<p>
				<strong>Tech:</strong> Python, LinkML, OWL/RDF, graph-based models, XSD/XML parsing.
			</p>
		</section>
	</main>
</Layout>

<style>
	main {
		max-width: 720px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 4rem 1.5rem;
	}

	header {
		margin-bottom: 4rem;
	}

	h1 {
		font-size: 2.5rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		margin: 0 0 1rem;
		letter-spacing: -0.02em;
	}

	.intro {
		font-size: 1.125rem;
		line-height: 1.7;
		color: #4b5563;
		margin: 0;
	}

	.research-entry {
		margin-bottom: 4rem;
		padding-bottom: 3rem;
		border-bottom: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
	}

	.research-entry:last-of-type {
		border-bottom: none;
	}

	h2 {
		font-size: 1.5rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
		letter-spacing: -0.01em;
	}

	.meta {
		display: flex;
		gap: 1rem;
		margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
		font-size: 0.875rem;
		color: #6b7280;
	}

	.meta a {
		color: #111827;
		text-decoration: none;
		font-weight: 500;
		border-bottom: 1px solid #111827;
		transition: opacity 0.2s;
	}

	.meta a:hover {
		opacity: 0.6;
	}

	.meta span:not(:last-child)::after {
		content: '•';
		margin-left: 1rem;
		color: #d1d5db;
	}

	.problem {
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
		line-height: 1.7;
	}

	.research-entry p {
		line-height: 1.7;
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
		color: #374151;
	}

	.research-entry p:last-of-type {
		margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
	}

	strong {
		font-weight: 600;
		color: #111827;
	}

	.links {
		display: flex;
		gap: 1rem;
	}

	.links a {
		color: #111827;
		text-decoration: none;
		font-weight: 500;
		border-bottom: 2px solid #111827;
		padding-bottom: 2px;
		transition: opacity 0.2s;
	}

	.links a:hover {
		opacity: 0.6;
	}

	.diagram {
		width: 100%;
		max-width: 600px;
		height: auto;
		margin: 0 0 2rem;
		padding: 1.5rem;
		background: rgba(249, 250, 251, 0.5);
		border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
		border-radius: 8px;
	}

	@media (max-width: 640px) {
		.diagram {
			padding: 1rem;
		}
		main {
			padding: 3rem 1.25rem;
		}

		h1 {
			font-size: 2rem;
		}

		.meta {
			flex-direction: column;
			gap: 0.25rem;
		}

		.meta span:not(:last-child)::after {
			display: none;
		}
	}
</style>

